"title": "7768: priests, function in OT times",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7768",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Priests had a unique role: administering the sanctuary, offering sacrifice and leading and teaching the people. Accordingly they were set apart by a special code of conduct.</p>\n<h2>The priests were set apart</h2>\n<h3>They were consecrated to the LORD</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:9\">LEV 22:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:1\">EXO 28:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:4\">EXO 28:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:41\">EXO 28:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:1\">EXO 29:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:44\">EXO 29:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:34\">EXO 30:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:10\">EXO 31:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:19\">EXO 35:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:41\">EXO 39:41</a></p>\n<h3>They were not to incur uncleanness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:1\">LEV 21:1</a></strong> <em>Some exceptions to uncleanness by touching a corpse are listed in verses 2–3.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:25\">EZK 44:25</a></p>\n<h3>They were not to shave or mutilate themselves</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:5\">LEV 21:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:20\">EZK 44:20</a></p>\n<h3>They were not to marry any but a virtuous Israelite</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:7\">LEV 21:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:22\">EZK 44:22</a></p>\n<h3>They were not to drink wine before entering the sanctuary</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:9\">LEV 10:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:21\">EZK 44:21</a></p>\n<h3>They were disqualified by physical defects</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:17\">LEV 21:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:18-Lev21:22\">LEV 21:18–21:22</a></p>\n<h3>They were not to allow outsiders to eat the sacred offerings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:15-Lev22:16\">LEV 22:15–22:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev24:9\">LEV 24:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam21:4\">1SA 21:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:4\">MAT 12:4</a></p>\n<h3>They were not to own land in Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:20\">NUM 18:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:28\">EZK 44:28</a></p>\n<h3>They were not to offer unacceptable sacrifices</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:20\">LEV 22:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:7-Mal1:9\">MAL 1:7–1:9</a></p>\n<h3>They were to obey God's law meticulously</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:31\">LEV 22:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:24\">EZK 44:24</a></p>\n<h2>The priests supervised the sanctuary</h2>\n<h3>They only had access to holy things</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:10\">NUM 3:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:5\">NUM 4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:45-Ezek40:46\">EZK 40:45–40:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:16\">EZK 44:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:17\">JOL 2:17</a></p>\n<h3>They tended the sanctuary lamps</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod27:21\">EXO 27:21</a></strong></p>\n<h3>They carried the ark</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:9\">DEU 31:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:8\">JOS 3:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:15\">JOS 3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:17\">JOS 3:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh4:9\">JOS 4:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh4:16\">JOS 4:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:12\">JOS 6:12</a></p>\n<h2>The priests supervised the sacrifices</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev1:5\">LEV 1:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev1:8\">LEV 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:2\">LEV 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:30\">1CH 9:30</a></p>\n<h2>The priests led the nation</h2>\n<h3>As role models</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:6\">MAL 2:6</a></strong></p>\n<h3>As teachers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:23\">EZK 44:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:10\">LEV 10:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:10-Deut31:13\">DEU 31:10–31:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra7:6\">EZR 7:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:7\">MAL 2:7</a></p>\n<h3>As judges</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:9\">DEU 17:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:17\">DEU 19:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:5\">DEU 21:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr19:8\">2CH 19:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:24\">EZK 44:24</a></p>\n<h3>As encouragers in battle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:8\">NUM 10:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:4\">JOS 6:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr13:12\">2CH 13:12</a></p>\n<h2>Prophetic criticism of the priests</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam4:13\">LAM 4:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:8\">JER 2:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:13\">JER 6:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek7:26\">EZK 7:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:26\">EZK 22:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:6-Hos4:9\">HOS 4:6–4:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:9\">HOS 6:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:4\">ZEP 3:4</a></p>",
